SEARCH
Package au.csiro.pathling.search.filter

Enum Class SearchPrefix

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<SearchPrefix>
au.csiro.pathling.search.filter.SearchPrefix
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<SearchPrefix>, Constable
public enum SearchPrefix extends Enum<SearchPrefix>
Represents comparison prefixes for ordered search parameters (date, number, quantity).

FHIR search values can be prefixed with comparison operators like "ge" (greater or equal), "lt" (less than), etc. If no prefix is specified, "eq" (equals) is assumed.

This enum handles only prefix extraction. Value validation is the responsibility of the type-specific matchers (DateMatcher, NumberMatcher, etc.).

    • parseValue

      @Nonnull public static SearchPrefix.ParsedValue parseValue(@Nonnull String value)
      Parses both the prefix and value from a search string in a single operation.

      This method is more efficient than calling fromValue(String) and stripPrefix(String) separately, as it executes the regex pattern only once.

      Parameters:
      value - the search value, possibly prefixed
      Returns:
      a ParsedValue containing both the extracted prefix and the remaining value

    • fromValue

      @Nonnull public static SearchPrefix fromValue(@Nonnull String value)
      Extracts the prefix from a search value.

      If the value starts with a recognized prefix (e.g., "ge2023-01-15" or "gt0.8"), returns the corresponding prefix. If no prefix is present, returns EQ as the default.

      Parameters:
      value - the search value, possibly prefixed
      Returns:
      the parsed prefix, or EQ if no prefix

    • stripPrefix

      @Nonnull public static String stripPrefix(@Nonnull String value)
      Removes the prefix from a search value, returning the value portion.

      If the value has a prefix (e.g., "ge2023-01-15"), returns the value part ("2023-01-15"). If no prefix is present, returns the original value unchanged.

      Parameters:
      value - the search value, possibly prefixed
      Returns:
      the value portion without the prefix
